This tool will return an object that contains fields for the creation of a stock chart.
The object contains the following fields: `dates`, `open`, `high`, `low`, `close`, and `caption`.
The `dates` field is an array of date strings representing the time series.
The `open`, `high`, `low`, and `close` fields are arrays of numbers representing the opening, highest, lowest, and closing prices corresponding to each date.
The `caption` field is a string that provides a brief description or title for the stock chart.
The first element in each array corresponds to the first date in the `dates` array, and so on.

